{"analytics_identifier":null,"base_path":"/government/people/georgia-gould","content_id":"d01cd743-767b-4057-8eba-3949fb11ff6a","description":"Georgia Gould was appointed Minister of State (Minister for School Standards) at the Department for Education on 6 September 2025. She was previously Parliamentary Secretary at the Cabinet Office between 9 July 2024 and 6 September 2025. Georgia was elected as the MP for Queen’s Park and Maida Vale in July 2024.","details":{"body":"<p>Georgia Gould was appointed Minister of State (Minister for School Standards) at the Department for Education on 6 September 2025.</p>\n\n<p>She was previously Parliamentary Secretary at the Cabinet Office between 9 July 2024 and 6 September 2025.</p>\n\n<p>Georgia was elected as the MP for Queen’s Park and Maida Vale in July 2024.</p>\n","full_name":"Georgia Gould OBE MP","image":{"alt_text":"Georgia Gould OBE MP","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/668fa9e849b9c0597fdafadb/s465_Untitled.jpg"},"privy_counsellor":false},"document_type":"person","first_published_at":"2024-07-09T19:01:27+01:00","links":{"available_translations":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/people/georgia-gould","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/people/georgia-gould","base_path":"/government/people/georgia-gould","content_id":"d01cd743-767b-4057-8eba-3949fb11ff6a","document_type":"person","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2025-09-22T11:53:06Z","schema_name":"person","title":"Georgia Gould OBE MP","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/georgia-gould","withdrawn":false}],"role_appointments":[{"content_id":"37d9ffe5-6fd6-449d-8756-c471cf08e583","details":{"current":true,"ended_on":null,"person_appointment_order":3,"started_on":"2025-09-06T00:00:00+01:00"},"document_type":"role_appointment","links":{"person":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/people/georgia-gould","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/people/georgia-gould","base_path":"/government/people/georgia-gould","content_id":"d01cd743-767b-4057-8eba-3949fb11ff6a","details":{"body":"<p>Georgia Gould was appointed Minister of State (Minister for School Standards) at the Department for Education on 6 September 2025.</p>\n\n<p>She was previously Parliamentary Secretary at the Cabinet Office between 9 July 2024 and 6 September 2025.</p>\n\n<p>Georgia was elected as the MP for Queen’s Park and Maida Vale in July 2024.</p>\n","image":{"alt_text":"Georgia Gould OBE MP","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/668fa9e849b9c0597fdafadb/s465_Untitled.jpg"}},"document_type":"person","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2025-09-22T11:53:06Z","schema_name":"person","title":"Georgia Gould OBE MP","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/georgia-gould","withdrawn":false}],"role":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/ministers/minister-of-state--187","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/ministers/minister-of-state--187","base_path":"/government/ministers/minister-of-state--187","content_id":"7afdbe17-ea80-463a-b7cd-4fa34db9c326","details":{"body":"<p>The minister’s responsibilities include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>school improvement, intervention and inspection (including links with <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/ofsted\">Ofsted</a>)</li>\n  <li>regional improvement for standards and excellence (RISE)</li>\n  <li>special educational needs and disabilities (SEND) and high needs</li>\n  <li>alternative provision</li>\n  <li>special schools (including independent special schools (ISS))</li>\n  <li>initial teacher training and incentives</li>\n  <li>teacher retention including the early career framework and teacher training entitlement</li>\n  <li>\n<a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/teaching-regulation-agency\">Teaching Regulation Agency</a> (TRA)</li>\n  <li>school leadership</li>\n  <li>school governance</li>\n  <li>teacher pay and pensions</li>\n  <li>school support staff</li>\n  <li>core school funding</li>\n  <li>pupil premium</li>\n  <li>school productivity</li>\n  <li>qualifications (including links with <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/ofqual\">Ofqual</a>)</li>\n  <li>national curriculum</li>\n  <li>access to sport, arts and music in education, working with other departments</li>\n  <li>admissions and pupil movement</li>\n  <li>relationships and sex education and health education (RSHE) review</li>\n</ul>\n\n","role_payment_type":null,"seniority":100,"whip_organisation":{}},"document_type":"ministerial_role","links":{"ordered_parent_organisations":[{"analytics_identifier":"D6","api_path":"/api/content/government/organisations/department-for-education","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/organisations/department-for-education","base_path":"/government/organisations/department-for-education","content_id":"ebd15ade-73b2-4eaf-b1c3-43034a42eb37","details":{"acronym":"DfE","brand":"department-for-education","default_news_image":{"high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69de23bb9af91e9ee4b2c327/s960_DfE_Sanctuary_Building_London_office.jpeg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69de23bb3e81003ae042250c/s300_DfE_Sanctuary_Building_London_office.jpeg"},"logo":{"crest":"single-identity","formatted_title":"Department <br/>for Education"},"organisation_govuk_status":{"status":"live","updated_at":null,"url":null}},"document_type":"organisation","links":{},"locale":"en","schema_name":"organisation","title":"Department for Education","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-education","withdrawn":false}]},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2026-05-15T17:16:09Z","schema_name":"role","title":"Minister of State (Minister for School Standards)","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/ministers/minister-of-state--187","withdrawn":false}]},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2025-09-22T11:52:44Z","schema_name":"role_appointment","title":"Georgia Gould MP - M